The lamb was great, tasty and pairing sauce was great. The portion does feel a little too small. Sangria was also nice but does feel a little overly-diluted. Will come back to try the arepa next time.

Food was tasty, but the service was not great. They brought it late, although I mentioned before ordering that I had to leave at a certain time and they said the food would be ready in time, which wasn‚Äôt the case. Also, when I asked if I could use the WiFi, the lady answered ‚Äúwe have WiFi but don‚Äôt share the password‚Äù‚Ä¶
Food and service were good, but we saw 2 huge rats on the patio
Great food, had the arepas , the chef made a special arrangement just for us.

First time eating Venezuelan food. At lunch, the service was a little slow. It took 25 mins to have our food but everything was delicious and flavorful. Trio De Empanadas, each dumplings have different flavors as shredded pork, cheese and black bean paste. Not many options on the lunch menu so I want to try their dinner menu next time.

Stumbled upon this place last night while trying to find somewhere good to eat for a late bday celebration. Our server was amazing- gave so many good recommendations and everything we tried was absolutely delicious. The sangria is a must try and the beef and cheese arepa was out of this world. We also tried the chicken and pork arepas, and the chicken and steak plate, and mini ribs. It was so delicious. it took about 45 minutes to bring the food which was a little bit cold. The people was very kind and attentive, shame what happened with the food.
Excellent empanadas
delish. yummylicious. scrumdiddlyumptious.

Everything ordered was good. Small and quaint. It‚Äôs in Harvard Square so keep in mind street parking is not the easiest. Only reason I didn‚Äôt give 5 stars is because they don‚Äôt have chicha on the menu :-). It‚Äôs like not having horchata at a Mexican restaurant.

My small group had a serendipitous experience at Orinoco. We walked around and happened to stumble on this place for dinner - it's definitely a hidden gem.

I loved the atmosphere; quiet so that I could talk to my group and not too bright or too dark. We ordered the tequenos, plantains, and ribs for appetizers; the latter two were totally delicious. Service was good but nothing spectacular and unfortunately they did not have Arepas that night.

For the main course I got the lamb chops and quinoa. Both were mind-blowingly delicious and cooked to perfection. This was the tastiest quinoa I ever had and a top-tier lamb dish with a delicious mint sauce. The prices were also very reasonable!

Overall highly satisfied with the meal and will definitely come back to try the Arepas.

I love this place! Great food, nice people and nice atmosphere. Try everything in special don‚Äôt forget to ask for the sangria!
so good!üëåüèº

We recently dined at this quaint spot in Harvard Square. We tried the Steak, the ribs, and the guava flatbread. The guava flatbread was a standout, however, the ribs and the steak didn't quite meet our expectations. The ribs were a bit tough to cut through, and the BBQ sauce, which was the same for both dishes, didn't quite hit the mark for us. We had ordered the steak cooked to medium, but it turned out a bit too chewy and overcooked. The staff kindly replaced it, and the second one came out cooked to a perfect medium, which we appreciated. In terms of beverage options, the selection was somewhat limited, with only wine and beer available. On a less positive note, we did observe a rat scurrying through the dining area, which was quite surprising and definitely detracted from the overall experience.

Edit based on owners question: Appreciate your prompt response. We were seated indoors in the dining room and saw what would be a ‚Äúmouse‚Äù, still pretty disturbing to see it run indoors along the outside wall of the bar
Also yeah, getting a heads up about our order would have been nice. All the 3 items we had ordered had some of the sauce, wish we got a heads up.
A hidden gem - venezualian cuisine at its best. Quite some vegetarian options as well!

Nice place to have arepas , not expensive I think prices are fair. Ocasssion : you are hanging up around Harvard university and wanna eat some latin tasty food and don‚Äôt want to go crazy with the budget.

Love this place! Found via Off the Beaten Path Food Tours, our group loved Orinoco. The atmosphere is really intimate, and the food is fresh and tasty. We tried cheese covered plantains and yummy bacon wrapped dates that were out of this world. The sangria was also incredible and our server was so kind! Highly recommend.
Visited for an event. Good food and service. Will visit again.

The website is misleading as it talks about prices potentially differing from the website but the tables just have QR codes that take you to another website with pricing that shows everything the restaurant is out of stock. Had a great time here for a rather large party.  I think the kitchen couldn‚Äôt keep up.  But the meals were good and served warm when they came out and the employees were all professionals and had good attitudes.

Everything was delicious and well priced. Service was great and I loved the atmosphere. Also not too busy on a Friday at 630PM which was ideal since I was very hungry when I got there. The red sangria is delicious, I suggest the pitcher because you WILL want more than one glass.

Tucked away in a little alleyway and had really nice cozy evening fairytale vibes! Tried the pelua arepa! Good cheese, meat and arepa corn bread(?)! It came with a really strong but incredible garlic sauce too!
Too expensive

Excellent vibe with friendly staff. The food was good, especially the ribs! Arepas are good, but won‚Äôt blow your mind. Could be a little more moist and the white sauce was quite garlicky. Yet we enjoyed our time and it‚Äôs a great find for Harvard square

It is gem in harvard square,

Surprisingly for a Latin place, my biggest recommendation is the baby back ribs. They are hands down the best I‚Äôve had in the Boston area (and I‚Äôm a bbq guy). The sauce is so delicious and complex. Also, the chicken in the Parrilla Caraque√±a was so moist and delicious. My girlfriend and I loved it.

A word of caution - if you sit outside in the back there‚Äôs a chance you may see a furry friend or two. Nothing to be worried about, but a fair warning. No fault of their own, as it‚Äôs a problem in the Cambridge/Somerville/south Medford area.

FYI - Pics taken by candlelight.

They had a large table to serve and they said that was the reason for the delay but even a packed restaurant is not a good reason for delays. I have worked as a waiter at 30 different restaurants and know that you have to be ready for busy days. Fortunately the food was great and if it came fast I'd say 5 stars for me. Great food and normal portion sizes

Wonderful food and service.
Fantastic good and great patio in back.
Very delicious food and warm atmosphere.
I was there on Thursday night. I met the lady at the front deck she was friendly and polite. I ordered date wrap with date and almond, flatbread oysters mushroom,baby rib, chulete Wonderful dinner,

It can be one of my list, first time to enjoy Latin food in Boston.
Very taste  nice service  nice little place
Prices a little high for a college student but great portions!!
Delicious food and great service with excellent location near the Harvard campus. We visited for lunch and ate outside to enjoy the warm weather

Orinoco was good, but other restaurants are better.

Orinoco has the misfortune of being a good restaurant surrounded by great ones. For hole-in-the-wall charm, I'd go to Pinocchio's Pizza or 9 Tastes Thai, both on the same block and at a lower price point. For great food, I'd go to Park, just across the street. Cafe
Food is delicious! I would recommend "costillitas"

While their name sounds more like a gas station, this is a cool little South American eatery tucked in an alley of Harvard Square. They have a diverse menu of a variety of arepas, empanadas, pepitos (sandwiches), and principales (main dishes). Many of these menu items are very authentic South American dishes that you would be hard-pressed to find in any other restaurant.
I personally would recommend sticking to the pepitos and principales, since I've found to be very wholesome and well thought-out plates. The empanadas are served with a central salad presentation and can be a bit dry and heavy.
For filling a rare culinary niche in Harvard Square, I would score the place 5 stars, but it can be challenging to get seats (no reservations) and their sometimes rather brusque service detracts one star.

The staff was friendly and service was fantastic. Plenty of vegetarian options for us to try. The arepas, empanadas, salad, and starters were delicious, and don't forget to ask for their amazing hot sauce!

Solid, fun place to eat! If the weather is nice, sit out back at their cute tables. I've been here two or three times and the service is always relatively fast. Solid spot for a wide variety of interesting dishes. Nice outdoor seating area in the back

:) sabroso

This place has so weird hours. They will close on your face at 1:45 pm like nothing. Has happened various times. Never going back.

This place was pretty good.  The empanadas, mechado, and ribs were well prepared. The meat sampler plate was decent. The server was nice.

Cozy place tucked into a hidden corner of Harvard Square. Delicious Venezuelan cuisine and excellent service in a warm atmosphere. Great
Friendly, efficient service, and an excellent portobello arepa!

no muy venezolano...s√≥lo el mesero (muy buena gente por cierto) lo era.
Baby back ribs meat falls off the bone, Delicious

Food: arepa pernil, trio de empanadas, parillo caraque√±a

I love this place for affordable, shared plates. The flavors here are amazing and the arepas and empanadas go so well with the mojo.

I appreciate that the fried plantains still had some bite to it and weren‚Äôt overly ripened or mushy, but still sweet - perfect for the pabell√≥n criollo plate. Lovely ambience on the back porch, a bit dimly lit, probably best for a date but great for literally any other occasion.
One of the best restaurants in Cambridge. If you‚Äôre in a rush, this is not the place for you. The food and sangria were incredible. Friendly people. Romantic patio.
The fried yucca is amazing, lots of good veggie options, nice outdoor space, friendly service.

In terms of arepas our favorites were 1. Pernil 2. Pabellon 3. Mechada. We tried all 8 of them and shared with a group of 4 and it was really fun, although you need everyone to be okay with sharing for this to work because they are not easily cut in 4ths.

The sangria pitcher is totally worth it! It's an incredible blend of wine, fruit, and cinnamon flavors that are out of this world. We also ordered the bacon wrapped dates, and they could score you a second date if you're lucky. Mileage may vary. 5 stars.

Small but suitable drink options: beer (2 kinds of Latin laggers), wine, and sangria. No hard alcohol, but no big deal. Service is very friendly.

Surprisingly for a Latin place, my biggest recommendation is the baby back ribs. They are hands down the best I‚Äôve had in the Boston area (and I‚Äôm a bbq guy). The sauce is so delicious and complex. Also, the chicken in the Parrilla Caraque√±a was so moist and delicious. My girlfriend and I loved it.

A word of caution - if you sit outside in the back there‚Äôs a chance you may see a furry friend or two. Nothing to be worried about, but a fair warning. No fault of their own, as it‚Äôs a problem in the Cambridge/Somerville/south Medford area.

While their name sounds more like a gas station, this is a cool little South American eatery tucked in an alley of Harvard Square. They have a diverse menu of a variety of arepas, empanadas, pepitos (sandwiches), and principales (main dishes). Many of these menu items are very authentic South American dishes that you would be hard-pressed to find in any other restaurant.
I personally would recommend sticking to the pepitos and principales, since I've found to be very wholesome and well thought-out plates. The empanadas are served with a central salad presentation and can be a bit dry and heavy.
For filling a rare culinary niche in Harvard Square, I would score the place 5 stars, but it can be challenging to get seats (no reservations) and their sometimes rather brusque service detracts one star.

the arepas are the highlight here. I recommend just ordering a few of these for the entire meal (2 per person is a moderate portion), the cheese on them was addictive! They also had some interestin appz, but I didn't get any of those.
This restaurant doesn't take reservations, and it's easy to see why. The food was fantastic. Turn up and try your luck. We were a group of six and got a table within twenty minutes.
A tad overlooked, but the awesome little restaurant has delicious everything (I love the mango ribs!) an incredible hot sauce and a patio that can't be beat in the summer.
I enjoyed the empanadas and palmito salad and of course the bacon wrapped dates. The cocktails are a treat, especially when enjoyed on the outside patio in summer.
Great atmosphere, but the food is just alright and nothing memorable.
No era lo que esperaba, pues la Sra. de la entrada fue muy grosera, sin embargo el camarero fue muy amable y servicial.
Great atmosphere, a little hidden, but very nice and friendly. The empanadas and arepas were amazing!

Cannot possible rave more about how great my experience here is. The food is fantastic and the choices numerous! Service is incredible (especially our server Esteban)! Cocktails and wine choices are also well selected. I highly recommend this place and all of its locations around the city!
Fantastic dining experience, true Venezuelan eatery with many options. Exceptional service and on point recommendations.
The mix of flavors of the Venezuelan food is amazing and they cook it well.
Quite a secluded place for dinner.

Tucked away in an alley, Orinoco creates a sense of timelessness in the middle of the city. A seating next to the fountain in their patio and traditional music successfully transports its guests to South America.
Highlights of the menu: Arepas, slow cooked pork and imported cheese with vibrant accompaniments/dressings, vegetarians will not be compromising with their appetite either! Fried plantains stuffed with cheese are a burst of surprise!
The best Venezuelan food in Cambridge
